1577
01:54:26,326 --> 01:54:30,626
- How about Max?
- Max I feel bad about.

1578
01:54:30,697 --> 01:54:34,155
He doesn't have too many other people
to talk to.

1579
01:54:34,234 --> 01:54:37,726
I'm probably his closest
human relationship in the world.

1580
01:54:42,141 --> 01:54:44,609
These are all records?

1581
01:54:44,677 --> 01:54:46,975
Those 78s you were talking about?

1582
01:54:47,046 --> 01:54:48,479
Yep.

1583
01:54:51,751 --> 01:54:54,743
So I've got no patience
for Hollywood bullshit.

1584
01:54:56,222 --> 01:54:59,817
I can't think in those terms.

1585
01:54:59,893 --> 01:55:04,296
I've already got so much of my life
wasted with those people down there.

1586
01:55:04,364 --> 01:55:08,300
Animation? Forget it. No.
I'm not interested in it at all.

1587
01:55:08,368 --> 01:55:12,464
There hasn't been a decent animated film
made in this country since 1940.

1588
01:55:12,538 --> 01:55:15,735
‘‘Cheery Pop Tart’’ is an abomination.

1589
01:55:15,808 --> 01:55:18,834
Larry Wells is an idiot.
It's going to be a piece of garbage.

1590
01:55:18,912 --> 01:55:21,710
I'm not interested.
All right.

1591
01:55:21,781 --> 01:55:23,214
So long.

1592
01:55:28,121 --> 01:55:32,421
I was on a conference call with Charles
Webb, a friend of Dan O'Neill's.

1593
01:55:32,492 --> 01:55:35,950
They're putting together
the ‘‘Cherry Pop Tart’’ film.

1594
01:55:36,029 --> 01:55:38,463
They got on the phone with
some guy in L.A. who says...

1595
01:55:38,531 --> 01:55:42,797
‘‘Hey! I'm your kind of guy.
Remember 'Tommy Toilet'? I love it!’’

1596
01:55:47,307 --> 01:55:49,468
They want to make a movie?

1597
01:55:49,542 --> 01:55:54,912
The natural film, of course.
It's a ‘‘go’’ project.

1598
01:55:56,983 --> 01:56:01,386
This is how I felt
after that last hell week...

1599
01:56:01,454 --> 01:56:04,150
of you filming me here.

1600
01:56:04,223 --> 01:56:07,818
‘‘How perfectly goddamned delightful
it all is, to be sure.’’

1601
01:56:07,894 --> 01:56:11,159
When I was a kid, if I ever started
showing enthusiasm for anything...

1602
01:56:11,230 --> 01:56:13,164
by brother Charles would say...

1603
01:56:13,232 --> 01:56:16,668
‘‘How perfectly goddamned delightful
it all is, to be sure.’’

1604
01:56:16,736 --> 01:56:19,569
Always take the wind
out of my sails.

1605
01:56:19,639 --> 01:56:22,267
Even though I don't see him often,
whenever I'm with him...

1606
01:56:22,342 --> 01:56:26,244
it revives that keen awareness
of that...

1607
01:56:26,312 --> 01:56:31,375
of being very removed
or extremely separated...

1608
01:56:31,451 --> 01:56:33,715
from the rest of humanity
and the world in general.

1609
01:56:33,786 --> 01:56:36,687
I kinda like that feeling.

1610
01:56:36,756 --> 01:56:40,317
‘‘How perfectly goddamned delightful
it all is, to be sure.’’

1611
01:57:14,060 --> 01:57:17,826
Fix it, Charles. Put back the towel
the way I had it.

1612
01:57:17,897 --> 01:57:19,831
First put the towel up.

1613
01:57:21,801 --> 01:57:24,463
Watch you don't pull the shade
all the way off the thing.

1614
01:57:24,537 --> 01:57:25,970
I won't.

1615
01:57:28,808 --> 01:57:32,244
Can't come in and disrupt
people's house like this!

1616
01:57:32,311 --> 01:57:33,471
Where are the babies?

1617
01:57:33,546 --> 01:57:35,878
I don't know. I think
that little girl is in my room.

